SuperSport United have confirmed the appointment of Kaitano Tembo as the club's new head coach. The 48-year oldwho was the assistant coach to Eric Tinkler was appointed as interim coach in March following Tinkler's departure. The club has then confirmed the Zimbabwean born mentor as their new head coach on permanent basis after agreeing to a two-year deal. Tembo joined Matsatsantsa A Pitori in 1999 as a player and was captain for four year. During his time the Club won the SAA Super 8 competition 2004 which is now known as MTN8 and the Absa Cup (Nedbank Cu) in 2005. He is one of the highest capped players at the Club, having played over 200 matches. "I’m honoured by the confidence the club has shown in me in giving me this great opportunity, Tembo said."This club has been the centre of my life for almost 20 years and I and my players will give everything we have to keep our run of success going."SuperSport United CEO Stanley Mathews said he was delighted to appoint Tembo - who has been a loyal club servant - as the new head coach"Kaitano epitomises what it means to be a club ma,"Mathews said. "He joined us as a player 19 years ago and has worked his way through our youth structures and subsequently into the first team as an assistant."He has steered us on a caretaker basis on three separate occasions and everyone at the club is committed to reciprocating his loyalty and his desire to win silverware."Club chairperson Khulu Sibiya added: "It’s a great challenge for Kaitano because he knows we have high standards at the club. We will all rally behind him to deliver success because above all its a team effort.   